2026-05-01T07:57:15.3145317Z             "body": "## Summary\nAdds a new `EnableDirectDns` configuration option that allows administrators to disable direct UDP/TCP DNS queries to authoritative nameservers and public resolvers (8.8.8.8, 1.1.1.1, 9.9.9.9). When disabled, checks that depend on direct DNS access are skipped instead of timing out, making the validator suitable for restricted network environments where only a configured recursive resolver is available.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n- **Configuration & Documentation**\n  - Added `EnableDirectDns` boolean setting (default: `true`) to `AppConfig` with comprehensive documentation in new `docs/configuration.md`\n  - Updated `README.md` to reference configuration documentation\n  - Added environment variable support via standard ASP.NET Core configuration pipeline\n\n- **Core Validation Logic**\n  - Added `EnableDirectDns` property to `ValidationOptions` class\n  - Updated checks that require direct DNS to skip gracefully when disabled:\n    - `NsLameDelegationCheck` — direct queries to authoritative nameservers\n    - `SoaSerialConsistencyCheck` — direct SOA queries\n    - `OpenResolverCheck` — direct queries to public resolvers\n    - `NsGlueRecordCheck` — direct queries to parent nameservers\n    - `DelegationConsistencyCheck` — direct queries to parent nameservers\n  - Each check returns a \"Skipped\" result with explanatory message when the feature is disabled\n\n- **Web UI & API**\n  - Added checkbox in main validation form (`index.html`) to allow per-request control\n  - Added checkbox in admin config panel (`config.html`) for server-wide defaults\n  - Updated JavaScript to track user overrides and respect server configuration\n  - Updated `/api/defaults` endpoint to expose the setting\n  - Updated `/api/validate` endpoints to accept and apply the option\n\n- **Application Startup**\n  - Updated `Program.cs` to read `EnableDirectDns` from configuration and propagate through default options\n\n- **CI/CD**\n  - Updated GitHub Actions workflow to skip CI on documentation-only changes\n  - Enhanced Docker image tagging strategy with clearer tag prefixes (`branch-`, `pr-`, `sha-`)\n  - Improved push eligibility logic to support same-repo PRs while preventing fork PR pushes\n\n- **Docker**\n  - Updated `.dockerignore` to exclude documentation files\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nThe feature follows the existing AND-logic pattern for server-wide kill-switches: when disabled in configuration, clients cannot re-enable it. User-level preferences are only applied if not overridden by server configuration, ensuring administrators can enforce network policies.\n\nChecks that depend on direct DNS access include propagation verification, lame delegation detection, SOA serial consistency, glue record validation, parent-side delegation checks, open-recursive-resolver detection, and AXFR zone transfers.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_017ZcBW2eo4UWGs8ST9XYgwc",
